originalText.text: I had Metlife for 6 months. I totaled my car, in August 2019, got a rental. Gavin, (Gavyn?), I'm assuming is a supervisor of some sort & is very very unprofessional and lacks customer service skills. I had called in regards to extending my rental car. A gentleman said that, yes, it could be done. I called back to arrange it and spoke to a very kind woman. She put me on hold after I was expecting to speak to a supervisor.  She got back on the phone and apologized and informed me "Honey. Honestly you'd be better off speaking to me. I went to ask him (Gavyn) about extending it and as soon as I told him your name he said "what the hell does she want". I felt bad for the lady considering the work environment.  Not to mention, less than two weeks after they totaled my car, my bf saw a gentleman driving my car! In the SAME condition it was after the accident.  I will never go back to Metlife.
